  "Bare bones: 6 months; normal: 4 months": "",
  "Bare bones: 3 months; normal: 2 months": "",
  "Bare bones: 8 months; normal: 5 months": "",
  "Bare bones runway: $8,800 / $2,200 = 4 months. Normal budget runway: $8,800 / $3,100 = 2.84 months. Knowing both numbers is critical: switching to bare bones spending during a crisis extends financial runway by over a month, buying valuable time to find new income.": "",
  "A couple divorces and splits $300,000 in assets. Each now maintains a separate household. Before divorce: combined expenses $6,000/month. After: each person's expenses are $4,200/month (70% of combined, since some costs like housing do not split in half). What is the per-person financial impact?": "",
